  <div class="text">
    <p>Flying is the most convenient way to travel long distances that would otherwise take hours and days. When flying, we don’t perceive distances as much as time spent.</p>
    <p>While travelling, local arrival time is usually more important than time at home. Let's imagine we fly from Los Angeles to New York City. Our plane takes off at 4pm PST and lands at midnight EST. Upon arrival, you usually go to bed, despite being 9pm at home, in Los Angeles. It appears like it took 8 hours, when in reality you only spent 5 hours on the plane. On the flight back however, if you leave New York City at noon, you arrive in Los Angeles at 3:30pm PST. It appears like a 3h30min flight!</p>
    <p>What does the United States look like from major airports? Let's have a look!</p>

    <h2 class="section-title">East vs West</h2>
    <p>The Atlantic and Pacific coasts are ones of the most populated regions in the United States. There are hundreds of flights per day crossing the four time zones of the contiguous United States.</p>
