  <div class="text margin-bottom-large">
    <h2 class="section-title">At the Edge of Time</h2>
    <p>The United States spans six time zones. When New Yorkers stop for lunch, tourists are still asleep in Hawaii.</p>
    <p>Things get weird when flying across time zones. When flying West, it feels like time is slowing down. And when flying East, it feels like time is speeding up.</p>
    <p>At the edge between two time zones, it’s possible to arrive at destination at an earlier (local time) than you took off. Take Detroit and Chicago for example.</p>
  </div>
